<emphasis box="[207,220,1564,1588]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2608">–</emphasis>
0.91 mm
</quantity>
, females ca. 
<quantity box="[463,561,1565,1589]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.6" pageId="16" pageNumber="2608" unit="mm" value="0.96">0.96 mm</quantity>
wide (EW), ca. 2.1 times as long as wide (CL/EW).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[160,1155,1494,1727]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2608">
Dorsal colouration (
<figureCitation box="[416,510,1599,1623]" captionStart="Figures 6–9" captionStartId="7.[160,235,1337,1360]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,148,1289]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[163,1153,142,1306]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 6–9. Habitus of the Grouvellinus species collected from the Tawan Hills Park. 6: G. luciaensis, sp. nov. (paratype male from Lucia River); 7: G. borneensis, sp. nov. (paratype male from Tawau River environment); 8: G. sp.1 (female from Tawau River environment); 9: G. sp.2 (female from Lucia River). Scale: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3666544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3666544/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="2608">Figure 6</figureCitation>
) almost entirely dark brown to black; legs paler, at least distal half of femora and claws golden brown; maxillary and labial palps dark golden brown; pubescence shiny yellowish, rather inconspicuous. Ventral side (
<figureCitation box="[982,1091,1669,1693]" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1168,1191]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1137]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[163,1153,142,1137]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 14. Grouvellinus luciaensis, sp. nov. (paratypes): (a) anteriodorsal aspect with pronotum; (b) anterioventral aspect with head and prosternum; (c) ventral aspect with prosternum and mesoventrite, (d) posterioventral aspect with metaventrite and ventrites 1–5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3666554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3666554/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="2608">Figure 14</figureCitation>
(b 
<emphasis box="[1112,1125,1668,1692]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2608">–</emphasis>
d)) dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[160,1156,142,1726]" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[266,371,142,166]" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1168,1191]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1137]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[163,1153,142,1137]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 14. Grouvellinus luciaensis, sp. nov. (paratypes): (a) anteriodorsal aspect with pronotum; (b) anterioventral aspect with head and prosternum; (c) ventral aspect with prosternum and mesoventrite, (d) posterioventral aspect with metaventrite and ventrites 1–5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3666554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3666554/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">Figure 14</figureCitation>
(a)) 
<quantity box="[415,573,142,166]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" metricValueMax="4.3" metricValueMin="3.9" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609" unit="mm" value="0.41" valueMax="0.43" valueMin="0.39">
0.39 
<emphasis box="[461,474,142,166]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">–</emphasis>
0.43 mm
</quantity>
wide (HW); ID 
<quantity box="[742,904,142,166]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609" unit="mm" value="0.215" valueMax="0.24" valueMin="0.19">
0.19 
<emphasis box="[789,802,142,166]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">–</emphasis>
0.24 mm
</quantity>
; disc of frons, clypeus, and anterior and lateral areas of labrum sparsely pubescent; clypeus with two pairs of conspicuous sublateroanterior setae and entire frontal and lateral margins of labrum densely pubescent; punctures small; intervals glabrous; except for rugulouse frontal portion bordering eyes. Frontoclypeal suture straight, distinct. Eyes moderately large (eye diameter smaller than ID), slightly protruding. Antennae genus-typical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[160,1156,142,1726]" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[318,422,350,374]" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1168,1191]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1137]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[163,1153,142,1137]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 14. Grouvellinus luciaensis, sp. nov. (paratypes): (a) anteriodorsal aspect with pronotum; (b) anterioventral aspect with head and prosternum; (c) ventral aspect with prosternum and mesoventrite, (d) posterioventral aspect with metaventrite and ventrites 1–5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3666554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3666554/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">Figure 14</figureCitation>
(a)) in males: 
<quantity box="[568,727,350,374]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.3" metricValueMax="5.4" metricValueMin="5.2" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609" unit="mm" value="0.53" valueMax="0.54" valueMin="0.52">
0.52 
<emphasis box="[614,627,350,374]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">–</emphasis>
0.54 mm
</quantity>
, in females: 
<quantity box="[861,1018,350,374]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="5.699999999999999" metricValueMin="5.3" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609" unit="mm" value="0.55" valueMax="0.57" valueMin="0.53">
0.53 
<emphasis box="[908,921,350,374]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">–</emphasis>
0.57 mm
</quantity>
long (PL); in males: 
<quantity box="[242,407,385,409]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6" metricValueMax="6.7" metricValueMin="6.5" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609" unit="mm" value="0.66" valueMax="0.67" valueMin="0.65">
0.65 
<emphasis box="[289,302,385,409]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">–</emphasis>
0.67 mm
</quantity>
, in females: 
<quantity box="[556,718,385,409]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8999999999999995" metricValueMax="7.199999999999999" metricValueMin="6.6000000000000005" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609" unit="mm" value="0.69" valueMax="0.72" valueMin="0.66">
0.66 
<emphasis box="[603,616,385,409]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">–</emphasis>
0.72 mm
</quantity>
wide (PW), wider than long (PL/PW), widest posterior 0 
<emphasis box="[376,389,419,443]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">–</emphasis>
0.3, distinctly narrower than elytra, anteriorly attenuate; anterior margin slightly convex; pronotal disc moderately vaulted; entire pronotum moderately sparsely punctate; punctures small and shallowly impressed; median carina absent; with a pair of small and moderately deep posterior-median pits (anterior of the scutellum); sublateral carinae distinct and short; oblique impression moderately deep, narrow and glabrous, extending approx. anterior 0.35 
<emphasis box="[634,647,593,617]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">–</emphasis>
0.65; laterobasal impression shallow, rugose; setae moderately short; interstices glabrous and flat. Hypomeron densely punctate, punctures large. Prosternum (
<figureCitation box="[496,603,662,686]" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1168,1191]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1137]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[163,1153,142,1137]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 14. Grouvellinus luciaensis, sp. nov. (paratypes): (a) anteriodorsal aspect with pronotum; (b) anterioventral aspect with head and prosternum; (c) ventral aspect with prosternum and mesoventrite, (d) posterioventral aspect with metaventrite and ventrites 1–5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3666554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3666554/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">Figure 14</figureCitation>
(b)) short; lateral portions with pubescence (plastron); median portion including process medially broadly impressed, slightly rugulose; prosternal process trapezoidal, slightly longer than wide, medially impressed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[160,1156,142,1726]" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">
Scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[316,421,766,790]" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1168,1191]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1137]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[163,1153,142,1137]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 14. Grouvellinus luciaensis, sp. nov. (paratypes): (a) anteriodorsal aspect with pronotum; (b) anterioventral aspect with head and prosternum; (c) ventral aspect with prosternum and mesoventrite, (d) posterioventral aspect with metaventrite and ventrites 1–5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3666554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3666554/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">Figure 14</figureCitation>
(a)) subtriangular, flat, glabrous. Elytra (
<figureCitation box="[855,946,766,790]" captionStart="Figures 6–9" captionStartId="7.[160,235,1337,1360]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,148,1289]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[163,1153,142,1306]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 6–9. Habitus of the Grouvellinus species collected from the Tawan Hills Park. 6: G. luciaensis, sp. nov. (paratype male from Lucia River); 7: G. borneensis, sp. nov. (paratype male from Tawau River environment); 8: G. sp.1 (female from Tawau River environment); 9: G. sp.2 (female from Lucia River). Scale: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3666544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3666544/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">Figure 6</figureCitation>
) elongate, subparallel anterior 0.15 
<emphasis box="[355,368,801,825]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">–</emphasis>
0.60, moderately convex dorsally, in males: 
<quantity box="[862,1022,801,825]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4249999999999998" metricValueMax="1.44" metricValueMin="1.41" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609" unit="mm" value="1.4249999999999998" valueMax="1.44" valueMin="1.41">
1.41 
<emphasis box="[907,920,801,825]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">–</emphasis>
1.44 mm
</quantity>
, in females: 
<quantity box="[160,314,835,860]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.46" metricValueMax="1.48" metricValueMin="1.44" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609" unit="mm" value="1.46" valueMax="1.48" valueMin="1.44">
1.44 
<emphasis box="[205,218,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">–</emphasis>
1.48 mm
</quantity>
long (EL), 1.5 
<emphasis box="[457,470,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">–</emphasis>
1.6 times as long as wide (EL/EW), widest in anterior half; apices narrow, distinctly separately rounded; with eight longitudinal, distinctly impressed rows of punctures (striae); stria 8 reaching only up to 0.4 posterior; punctures somewhat regularly arranged, distinctly larger (diameter larger than interstices) and very deeply impressed in anterior and lateral portions, increasingly shallower and smaller apicad; interstices glabrous to finely rugulouse; median elytral portion, especially along interval 1 with additional very small setiferous secondary punctures; pubescence inconspicuous, consisting of very small adpressed setae and moderately large erected setae; interval 8 evenly carinate, but not serrate; interval 7 very slightly carinate; interval 5 (and intervals 
<quantity box="[849,916,1113,1137]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" metricValueMax="10.16" metricValueMin="5.08" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609" unit="in" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">
2 
<emphasis box="[862,875,1113,1137]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">–</emphasis>
4 in
</quantity>
lesser extent) broadly elevated in subanterior portion; lateral elytral margin carinate with fine serration.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[160,1156,142,1726]" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">
Mesoventrite (
<figureCitation box="[356,465,1182,1206]" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1168,1191]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1137]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[163,1153,142,1137]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 14. Grouvellinus luciaensis, sp. nov. (paratypes): (a) anteriodorsal aspect with pronotum; (b) anterioventral aspect with head and prosternum; (c) ventral aspect with prosternum and mesoventrite, (d) posterioventral aspect with metaventrite and ventrites 1–5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3666554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3666554/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">Figure 14</figureCitation>
(c)) with two pairs of shallow grooves behind procoxae and medially, respectively. Metaventrite (
<figureCitation box="[591,704,1217,1241]" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1168,1191]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1137]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[163,1153,142,1137]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 14. Grouvellinus luciaensis, sp. nov. (paratypes): (a) anteriodorsal aspect with pronotum; (b) anterioventral aspect with head and prosternum; (c) ventral aspect with prosternum and mesoventrite, (d) posterioventral aspect with metaventrite and ventrites 1–5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3666554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3666554/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">Figure 14</figureCitation>
(d)) moderately densely punctate, less densely at disc; longitudinal impression along entire median suture; lateral portions rather flat with inconspicuous plastron and a row of large punctures behind mesocoxae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[160,1156,142,1726]" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">
Ventrite 1 (
<figureCitation box="[315,422,1321,1345]" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1168,1191]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1137]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[163,1153,142,1137]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 14. Grouvellinus luciaensis, sp. nov. (paratypes): (a) anteriodorsal aspect with pronotum; (b) anterioventral aspect with head and prosternum; (c) ventral aspect with prosternum and mesoventrite, (d) posterioventral aspect with metaventrite and ventrites 1–5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3666554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3666554/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">Figure 14</figureCitation>
(d)) with pair of longitudinal carinae bordering disc; disc glabrous, sparsely punctate; lateral portions inconspicously pubescent (plastron); broad lateral portions of ventrites 1 
<emphasis box="[422,435,1390,1414]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">–</emphasis>
4 and almost entire ventrite 5 (
<figureCitation box="[809,920,1390,1414]" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1168,1191]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1137]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[163,1153,142,1137]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 14. Grouvellinus luciaensis, sp. nov. (paratypes): (a) anteriodorsal aspect with pronotum; (b) anterioventral aspect with head and prosternum; (c) ventral aspect with prosternum and mesoventrite, (d) posterioventral aspect with metaventrite and ventrites 1–5." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3666554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3666554/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">Figure 14</figureCitation>
(d)) densely covered with rather inconspicuous micro-plastron; ventrite 5 densely covered with setiferous tubercles and with apical fringe of moderately long setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[160,1156,142,1726]" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">
Legs (
<figureCitation box="[254,340,1494,1518]" captionStart="Figures 6–9" captionStartId="7.[160,235,1337,1360]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,148,1289]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[163,1153,142,1306]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 6–9. Habitus of the Grouvellinus species collected from the Tawan Hills Park. 6: G. luciaensis, sp. nov. (paratype male from Lucia River); 7: G. borneensis, sp. nov. (paratype male from Tawau River environment); 8: G. sp.1 (female from Tawau River environment); 9: G. sp.2 (female from Lucia River). Scale: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3666544" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3666544/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="2609">Figure 6</figureCitation>
) approximately as long as body; hindleg longest; tibia longer than tarsus and femur in all legs; proximal portion of mesofemur with loose fringe of moderately long trichoid setae at anterior-dorsal ridge (in both sexes); distal area of all tibiae with more or less densely covered with short trichoid setae; hind tibia additionally with loose longitudinal fringe of robust spine-like setae; coxae, trochanter, and particularly inner and posterior faces of femora and tibiae covered with conspicuous plastron setae. Legs not conspicuously varying between sexes.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3666554" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3666554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3666554/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="2610" startId="18.[160,225,1168,1191]" targetBox="[163,1153,142,1137]" targetPageId="18">
<paragraph blockId="18.[160,1156,1168,1250]" pageId="18" pageNumber="2610">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,265,1168,1191]" pageId="18" pageNumber="2610">Figure 14.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Freitag &amp; Molls &amp; Bouma &amp; Garces &amp; Rossato &amp; Cosentino &amp; Delledonne, 2019" authorityName="Freitag &amp; Molls &amp; Bouma &amp; Garces &amp; Rossato &amp; Cosentino &amp; Delledonne" authorityYear="2019" box="[273,490,1168,1191]" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Grouvellinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="2610" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luciaensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[273,490,1168,1191]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2610">
<taxonomicName box="[273,390,1168,1191]" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Grouvellinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="2610" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Grouvellinus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName box="[399,490,1168,1191]" pageId="18" pageNumber="2610" rank="species" species="luciaensis" status="sp. nov.">luciaensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[504,588,1168,1191]" pageId="18" pageNumber="2610" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[504,583,1168,1191]" pageId="18" pageNumber="2610">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(paratypes): (a) anteriodorsal aspect with pronotum; (b) anterioventral aspect with head and prosternum; (c) ventral aspect with prosternum and mesoventrite, (d) posterioventral aspect with metaventrite and ventrites 1 
<emphasis box="[806,819,1227,1250]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="2610">–</emphasis>
5.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="18.[160,1156,1322,1727]" pageId="18" pageNumber="2610">
Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[323,436,1322,1346]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="19.[160,225,1527,1550]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1496]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[163,1153,142,1496]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 15. Grouvellinus luciaensis, sp. nov. (paratypes): (a) aedeagus, lateral; (b) aedeagus, ventral; (c) ovipositor (half), ventral. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3666556" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3666556/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="2610">Figure 15</figureCitation>
(a,b)) ca. 635 μm long, ca. 190 μm wide. Base reaching basal 0.38 of total aedeagus length. Median lobe ca. four times as long as wide, moderately overreaching parameres, abruptly tapering in apical third towards the slender conical, rounded apex. Ventral sac apically inflated overreaching median lobe and parameres, internally densely stippled and with dense submedian fringes of moderately long, thin spines; apically the spines get longer and reach the apical opening. Parameres apically moderately conical (in both, ventral and lateral view), usually with more than 50 trichoid setae in apical two-third, most of them at the outer ventral face; most apical two setae longest and inserted at the apex. Male sternite IX as in previous new species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[160,1156,1322,1727]" lastBlockId="19.[160,1155,1627,1721]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="2611" pageId="18" pageNumber="2610">
Ovipositor (
<figureCitation box="[325,434,1669,1693]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="19.[160,225,1527,1550]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1496]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[163,1153,142,1496]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 15. Grouvellinus luciaensis, sp. nov. (paratypes): (a) aedeagus, lateral; (b) aedeagus, ventral; (c) ovipositor (half), ventral. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3666556" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3666556/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="2610">Figure 15</figureCitation>
(c)) total length ca. 790 μm; stylus ca. 40 μm long, moderately bent outwards with three short sensilla; coxite ca. 375 μm long with scattered extremely short, acute setae and four hook-like bent sensilla, apically moderately broadened at outer margin, valvifer ca. 430 μm long, caudal portion slightly sclerotised and with very few scattered, extremely short, acute setae; fibula almost straight.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3666556" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3666556" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3666556/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="2611" startId="19.[160,225,1527,1550]" targetBox="[163,1153,142,1496]" targetPageId="19">
<paragraph blockId="19.[160,1155,1526,1580]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2611">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,1527,1550]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2611">Figure 15.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Freitag &amp; Molls &amp; Bouma &amp; Garces &amp; Rossato &amp; Cosentino &amp; Delledonne, 2019" authorityName="Freitag &amp; Molls &amp; Bouma &amp; Garces &amp; Rossato &amp; Cosentino &amp; Delledonne" authorityYear="2019" box="[269,483,1526,1549]" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Grouvellinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="2611" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luciaensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[269,483,1526,1549]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="2611">Grouvellinus luciaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[494,576,1527,1550]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2611" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[494,571,1527,1550]" pageId="19" pageNumber="2611">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(paratypes): (a) aedeagus, lateral; (b) aedeagus, ventral; (c) ovipositor (half), ventral. Scale bar = 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="20.[160,995,142,202]" box="[160,388,142,167]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,388,142,167]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612">Sexual dimorphism</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[160,995,142,202]" box="[160,995,178,202]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612">Females with separately rounded and slightly more pointed elytral apices.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[160,1155,246,583]" box="[160,413,246,271]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,413,246,271]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[160,1155,246,583]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612">
<taxonomicName authority="Freitag &amp; Molls &amp; Bouma &amp; Garces &amp; Rossato &amp; Cosentino &amp; Delledonne, 2019" authorityName="Freitag &amp; Molls &amp; Bouma &amp; Garces &amp; Rossato &amp; Cosentino &amp; Delledonne" authorityYear="2019" box="[160,405,281,306]" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Grouvellinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luciaensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[160,405,281,306]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612">Grouvellinus luciaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[412,498,282,306]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from all known Bornean 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Champion" authorityYear="1923" box="[1021,1155,281,306]" class="Insecta" family="Elmidae" genus="Grouvellinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1021,1155,281,306]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612">Grouvellinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. by its moderately large size (CL) of 
<quantity box="[611,769,316,340]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.975" metricValueMax="2.04" metricValueMin="1.91" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612" unit="mm" value="1.975" valueMax="2.04" valueMin="1.91">
1.91 
<emphasis box="[657,670,316,340]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612">–</emphasis>
2.04 mm
</quantity>
(vs. ≤ 
<quantity box="[836,924,316,340]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612" unit="mm" value="1.9">1.9 mm</quantity>
, or ≥ 
<quantity box="[981,1068,316,340]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
), somewhat straight conical elytral posterior portion, very deeply impressed elytral striae in anterior and lateral portions, and a non-serrate 8th elytral interval. Furthermore, it is recognisable by the slight and uniform reddish-brownish tinge of the body, comparably pale femora, the aedeagal median lobe that is abruptly tapering in apical third and the comparably broad parameres with more than 50 trichoid setae in apical two-third.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[160,1155,246,583]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612">
The species varies by about 11 
<emphasis box="[539,552,524,548]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612">–</emphasis>
17% genetic distance (654 bp CO1 barcode) from the Bornean congeners.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="2612" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="20.[160,1156,628,722]" box="[160,300,628,653]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,300,628,653]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[160,1156,628,722]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612">
This species is only known from the 
<typeStatus box="[589,639,663,687]" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612">type</typeStatus>
locality, upper Lucia River, Tawau Hills Park, Sabah, Borneo Island (
<figureCitation box="[411,516,698,722]" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="25.[160,225,1675,1698]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,977,1643]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[163,1153,977,1643]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figure 18. Map of Sabah and Brunei (Borneo) with collecting site of Grouvellinus species with new species record in red fonts." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3666562" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3666562/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="2612">Figure 18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
